      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Feature scaling is crucial because algorithms like linear models, support vector machines, and neural networks use distance or gradient calculations that can be heavily biased by the magnitude of features. Since income (up to 500k) is roughly 60 times larger than the variance of age (up to 80), the model might incorrectly weigh income more heavily than age, even if both are equally important. Without scaling, the learning process becomes inefficient with larger gradients, potentially slowing down convergence or preventing the model from finding the optimal solution.",
